	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>Articles of Agreement between <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName> of the one part<lb/> and the Portuguese Jewish Congregation of the City of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> incorporated by the name&#44; style and title of <add>Hebrew</add> Kohel Radosh<lb/> Mikveh Israel of the other part made and entered into at the City of <placeName>Phi<lb/>ladelphia</placeName> on the <date>twenty second day of the month of Kislev in the year 5598</date>&#44; corresponding<lb/> with the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> day of December 1837</date> as follows to wit.</p>
				<p>First.  The said <persName role="author">Isaac</persName> covenants on his part to officiate and serve as <add>Hebrew</add> or Reader<lb/> to the said congregation for at least one year from the <date>first day of the Jewish month Tishry</date><lb/> last part&#44; corresponding with the <date>thirtieth day of September 1837</date> now last past&#44; and<lb/> for so much longer of a period of two years&#44; being a period of three years for which<lb/> he has been elected&#44; in case the difference of salary <del>of</del> now in dispute between<lb/> him and the congregation be properly adjusted&#44; during which continuance in office<lb/> he will faithfully <sic>fulfil</sic> the duties usually incident to said station&#44; that he will on every <date>Sabbath</date><lb/> eve&#44; morning and night&#44; and on all the holy days &#38; festivals&#44; and such other times<lb/> when the Synagogue is open for worship attend at the Synagogue and then &#38; there<lb/> in a devout manner read the prayers in the original Hebrew language&#44;<lb/> according to the custom of the Portuguese Jews&#59; that he will attend the funerals<lb/> &#40;under proper limitation&#41; that take place in the burial ground of the congregation<lb/> and perform the funeral and subsequent mourning service&#59; that he will not<lb/> at any time perform any marriage or funeral rites without the consent<lb/> of the Parnass or of the Adjunta&#59; that he will support and abide by the<lb/> Charter and Bylaws of the congregation&#59; and that he will obey the orders of<lb/> the Parnass or Segan<add>&#63;</add> in the Synagogue with regard to calling up and<lb/> distribution of the Mitzvote&#44; and never absent himself for more than<lb/> twenty four hours without the knowledge and consent of the Parnass&#44; or in<lb/> his absence the senior Adjunta.</p>
				<p>Second&#58;  In consideration of the said services the said congregation agrees<lb/> to pay him the sum of eight hundred Dollars pr annum unless otherwise ordered<lb/> by a meeting of the congregation&#44; in quarterly payments of two hundred each<lb/> or in an increased proportionate sum on the <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of March</date>&#44; <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of June</date><lb/> <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of September</date> and <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of December</date> in each and every year&#44; or when lawfully</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>thereafter demanded by said <persName role="author">Isaac</persName> <add>&#63;</add> for the due and faithful performance<lb/> of the foregoing covenant each party do the hereby  bind himself unto the other<lb/> in the penal sum of one thousand Dollars.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In witness whereof the said <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName> hath hereunto set his<lb/> hand &#38; seal&#44; and the said Kabal Kadosh Mikveh Israel have hereunto<lb/> caused their common corporate seal to be affixed attached by their<lb/> Parnass and Secretary&#44; the day and year first hereinbefore written</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
